52.body:
When the installion is finished, we will change some config file of Apache. So,change to the Apache's config directory. cd $PREFIX/etc/apache2/conf.d Create the php.conf config file. nano php.conf Add the following source code to load the PHP module from $PREFIX/libexec/apache2/libphp.so and save it. LoadModule php_module libexec/apache2/libphp.so
<FilesMatch \.php$> SetHandler application/x-httpd-php
</FilesMatch>
<IfModule dir_module> DirectoryIndex index.php
</IfModule> php.conf We will include the new config file to the httpd.conf. cd $PREFIX/etc/apache2
nano httpd.conf Go to the end of httpd.conf file and remove #. Note - # is a comment. #Include etc/apache2/conf.d/*.conf httpd.conf Find the worker module of PHP that does not need for us. CTRL+W and type worker and Enter. LoadModule mpm_worker_module libexec/apache2/mod_mpm_worker.so php.conf Add #. LoadModule mpm_worker_module libexec/apache2/mod_mpm_worker.so Find prefork module and remove #. #LoadModule mpm_prefork_module libexec/apache2/mod_mpm_prefork.so php.conf When we did the setting up of the config files, we will need to restart the Apache. apachectl restart # restart the Apache Server If we got the following error, ~ apachectl restart
httpd not running, trying to start Start the Apache Server. apachectl start # to start the server
apachectl restart # to restart the server By default,Apache Server is running on localhost:8080 (or) 127.0.0.7:8080. To stop the Apache just run the following command. apachectl stop # to stop the Apache If you got the servername error open httpd.conf file and search ServerName and edit like below. ServerName localhost:8080 php.conf Restart the server and try again. Open Browser and search the address localhost:8080 you will see It work!.It is the default page of Apache. We can change the server's root directory. Open httpd.conf and search the DocumentRoot and change the server's directory like below. DocumentRoot "/sdcard/htdocs"
<Directory "/sdcard/htdocs"> php.conf /sdcard/htdocs - is a directory in the Internal Storage of Android device. You can edit the directory path any time what you like but you must not add the / at the foreward of closing double quote. You will need to mount the internal storage by running this command. termux-setup-storage # mount the internal storage Create the new directory named htdocs in the internal storage and create a new php file like below. cd /sdcard/htdocs # go to the htdocs that is under the internal storage
echo "<?php echo 'Hello World!' ?>" > index.php Restart the server and search localhost:8080 in the browser and you will see Hello World!.
52.breadcrumbs: LAMP Setup Â» Setting Up The PHP and Apache
52.title: Setting Up The PHP and Apache

MongoDB is not officially support for aarch64 and some CPUs of Android. First of all , we will download itspointless repo's setup.sh to install their deps (dependencies) to our environment. # Download `setup-pointless-repo.sh`
wget https://its-pointless.github.io/setup-pointless-repo.sh bash setup-pointless-repo.sh Install the Mongodb by running following command. pkg i mongodb # to install mongodb When installation is finished, create path to store data of MongoDB. # setup the database storage directory for mongodb
mkdir -p /data/data/com.termux/files/usr/data/db Check Work Well or Not # Test the mongodb
~ mongod --version db version v4.1.13
git version: nogitversion
OpenSSL version: OpenSSL 1.1.1i 8 Dec 2020
allocator: system
modules: none
build environment: distarch: aarch64 target_arch: aarch64 If work test like below. # start the `mongodb` server
mongod Open new Session. # Connect with `mongodb` Client to mongodb server
mongo Testing > show dbs
admin 0.000GB
config 0.000GB
local 0.000GB
travel 0.000GB
> If you face libiary error,check the link below. Common Errors of Mongo DB

62.body:
# install the deps
pkg i clang cmake python -y # download `libicu67` archieve
wget https://github.com/unicode-org/icu/releases/download/release-67-1/icu4c-67_1-src.tgz # Extract (Unzip) `tar` archieve
tar -xf icu4c-67_1-src.tgz cd icu/source ./configure --prefix=$PREFIX # Check dependencies are exist or not (it will take long time be patient)
make # Compile the source code of `icu`
make install cd lib # `lib` directory stores compiled executable files # Move all compiled executable files to the `$PREFIX/usr/lib` directory
mv * $PREFIX/usr/lib # start the `mongodb` server
mongod Open new Session. # Connect with `mongodb` Client to mongodb server
mongo Testing > show dbs
admin 0.000GB
config 0.000GB
local 0.000GB
travel 0.000GB
>

62.title: Compile The icu Library
